5:
Wow, I can hardly believe this is the 
same city we saw before!
9: Yeah, it's a hell of a lot livelier.
14:
Hoo boy, it's sure changed a lot since 
the last time I was here.
18:
But first things first—It was a long walk 
over here, and I'm old and hungry. 
Time to explore the local cuisine!
23:
He better not make a fuss like LAST 
time he dragged us to lunch.
30:
Mm, this is really good! It's pretty 
different to how the catfolk make it.
32:
I suppose they've stepped up their 
game a liiittle since the last time I was 
here, I'll give 'em that.
40:
You know what? Look at Alk's 
compared to mine. I think the cook's 
adjusted the seasoning for me!
43:
It's nice seeing the dogfolk and catfolk 
getting along so well—all thanks to our 
dashing hero, King Whitetail.
47:
Can it. Butter me up all you like, I'm not 
paying for you.
51:
Tch. It was worth a sho—I mean, I don't 
know what you mean.
53:
Well, even if things are going well on 
the surface, I'm sure we've still got 
work to re—
68:
Drag that shill Albert out here, or this 
bloke gets it!
70: W-what are you doing this for?!
72:
To set 'im straight! We're not 'aving 
any of this peace treaty tripe.
73:
Yeah! One second the king sends us 
off to fight, then the next it's "never 
mind, let's all be beeest fwiends with 
the kitty-witties!"
80:
Bein' big babies. Hmph. No matter 
where you go, there'll always be guys 
like this.
83:
Times change faster than people. 
*sigh* Hey! You there!
90:
S-sir, please stay back! The guards will 
handle this!
92: Bah, I know what I'm doing.
97: Just an old cat who's seen enough.
101:
Let that young man go. You can take 
me hostage instead—I'd make a better 
one anyhow.
104:
What do you think'd make a bigger 
statement for your cause? Cutting 
down one of your own countrymen, or 
a helpless old feline?
107:
Hmph. Fine. You got off lucky, brat. 
Now git.
114:
I'll be fine. Better an old man like me 
than someone with so much more 
ahead of them.
116:
Remember me, young Whitetail. Not 
for my sacrifice—but as a warning that 
peace never comes without a price—
122:
Yeah, yeah, spare us the speech. If 
you're gonna zap 'em, get on with it.
126:
Oh, phooey, let a geezer enjoy his 
heroic speech.
133:
And I told you a billion times, the 
name's Nimbus! NIMBUS!
136:
And world peace or whatever's over 
my head. If my friends need help, I'll 
save 'em. If I see someone causing 
trouble, I'll deck 'em.
139:
Hah, kids. Only care about the here 
and now.
154:
I meant what I said back there, so 
don't you forget it.
159:
I might've BEEN Selenius Whitetail, but 
now... Now I'm me. Just Nimbus. Not 
the guy you're lookin' for.
164:
Oh, I don't know about that. I believe 
I'M the one who decides what I'm 
looking for.
170:
"If my friends need help, I'll save 'em. If 
I see someone causing trouble, I'll deck 
'em."
171:
I'm curious to see how far that 
sentiment will carry you.
181:
Never you mind. You do what you 
want, and I'll do what I want. Which at 
the moment, is helping you kids!
